Document: Gradient
Path: godot/classes/class_gradient.rst
Summary: Defines the properties of the Gradient class, including its colors, interpolation color space, interpolation mode, and offsets.

Properties
* colors (PackedColorArray): The array of colors defining the gradient. Default: PackedColorArray(0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1)
* interpolation_color_space (ColorSpace): The color space used for interpolation between colors. Default: 0
* interpolation_mode (InterpolationMode): The interpolation mode used between colors. Default: 0
* offsets (PackedFloat32Array): The array of offsets for each color in the gradient. Default: PackedFloat32Array(0, 1)
---CHUNK---
Document: Gradient
Path: godot/classes/class_gradient.rst
Summary: Defines the methods available for manipulating Gradient objects, including adding, getting, and setting points, as well as sampling and reversing the gradient.

Methods
Method: add_point(offset: float, color: Color)
Method: get_color(point: int) → Color
Method: get_offset(point: int) → float
Method: get_point_count() → int
Method: remove_point(point: int)
Method: reverse()
Method: sample(offset: float) → Color
Method: set_color(point: int, color: Color)
Method: set_offset(point: int, offset: float)

Enumerations
enum InterpolationMode:
  GRADIENT_INTERPOLATE_LINEAR = 0
    Linear interpolation.
  GRADIENT_INTERPOLATE_CONSTANT = 1
    Constant interpolation, color changes abruptly at each point and stays uniform between. This might cause visible aliasing when used for a gradient texture in some cases.
  GRADIENT_INTERPOLATE_CUBIC = 2
    Cubic interpolation.

enum ColorSpace:
  GRADIENT_COLOR_SPACE_SRGB = 0
    sRGB color space.
  GRADIENT_COLOR_SPACE_LINEAR_SRGB = 1
    Linear sRGB color space.
  GRADIENT_COLOR_SPACE_OKLAB = 2
    Oklab color space. This color space provides a smooth and uniform-looking transition between colors.
---CHUNK---
Document: Gradient
Path: godot/classes/class_gradient.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the Gradient class, including its colors, interpolation settings, and offsets.

Property: colors
Type: PackedColorArray
Description: Gradient's colors as a PackedColorArray.
Note: Setting this property updates all colors at once. To update any color individually use set_color().
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedColorArray for more details.
Setget:
- void set_colors(value: PackedColorArray)
- PackedColorArray get_colors()

Property: interpolation_color_space
Type: ColorSpace
Description: The color space used to interpolate between points of the gradient. It does not affect the returned colors, which will always use nonlinear sRGB encoding.
Note: This setting has no effect when interpolation_mode is set to GRADIENT_INTERPOLATE_CONSTANT.
Setget:
- void set_interpolation_color_space(value: ColorSpace)
- ColorSpace get_interpolation_color_space()

Property: interpolation_mode
Type: InterpolationMode
Description: The algorithm used to interpolate between points of the gradient.
Setget:
- void set_interpolation_mode(value: InterpolationMode)
- InterpolationMode get_interpolation_mode()

Property: offsets
Type: PackedFloat32Array
Description: Gradient's offsets as a PackedFloat32Array.
Note: Setting this property updates all offsets at once. To update any offset individually use set_offset().
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedFloat32Array for more details.
Setget:
- void set_offsets(value: PackedFloat32Array)
- PackedFloat32Array get_offsets()
---CHUNK---
Document: Gradient
Path: godot/classes/class_gradient.rst
Summary: Methods for manipulating and querying gradient points and colors.
Method: add_point(offset: float, color: Color)
Adds the specified color to the gradient, with the specified offset.
Method: get_color(point: int) → Color
Returns the color of the gradient color at index point.
Method: get_offset(point: int) → float
Returns the offset of the gradient color at index point.
Method: get_point_count() → int
Returns the number of colors in the gradient.
Method: remove_point(point: int)
Removes the color at index point.
Method: reverse()
Reverses/mirrors the gradient.
Note: This method mirrors all points around the middle of the gradient, which may produce unexpected results when interpolation_mode is set to GRADIENT_INTERPOLATE_CONSTANT.
Method: sample(offset: float) → Color
Returns the interpolated color specified by offset. offset should be between 0.0 and 1.0 (inclusive). Using a value lower than 0.0 will return the same color as 0.0, and using a value higher than 1.0 will return the same color as 1.0. If your input value is not within this range, consider using @GlobalScope.remap on the input value with output values set to 0.0 and 1.0.
Method: set_color(point: int, color: Color)
Sets the color of the gradient color at index point.
Method: set_offset(point: int, offset: float)
Sets the offset for the gradient color at index point.